  "text": "A detailed study of the background cosmology in this cosmological setting can be found in [29, [CITATION_1] . Several possible branches of the solutions are possible, depending on the initial values for r. In [CITATION_2] , a series of conditions defining a viable cosmological evolution are elaborated. Violations of these conditions do not necessarily imply contradiction with observations if they occur outside the observable range, hence in principle they can be relaxed or lifted. However, when these conditions are satisfied, the cosmological evolution requires no special tuning and it is much safer.",
